Luminoveau — LUMI_NO_GAMEPAD escape hatch for Input init
========================================================

Additive, opt-in. File touched:

    src/platform/input/input.cpp

SDL_Init(SDL_INIT_GAMEPAD) can hang indefinitely on some macOS setups (HID /
GameController enumeration stall), which blocks the whole app at startup. This adds
an escape hatch: set the env var LUMI_NO_GAMEPAD=1 to skip the gamepad/joystick
subsystem entirely — keyboard + mouse still work. Default (unset) is unchanged.

The MOUSE_KB InputDevice registration is moved above the early return so keyboard/
mouse are always available even when the gamepad init is skipped.

To apply (from the engine repo root):
    git apply luminoveau-input-no-gamepad.patch      # or: patch -p1 < ...

--- 8< --- patch below --- 8< ---

diff --git a/src/platform/input/input.cpp b/src/platform/input/input.cpp
index a55cd6e..88e3539 100644
--- a/src/platform/input/input.cpp
+++ b/src/platform/input/input.cpp
@@ -9,6 +9,13 @@ void Input::_init() {
 
     _didInit = true;
 
+    inputs.push_back(new InputDevice(InputType::MOUSE_KB));
+
+    // Escape hatch: SDL_Init(SDL_INIT_GAMEPAD) can hang indefinitely on some macOS
+    // setups (HID/GameController enumeration stall). Set LUMI_NO_GAMEPAD=1 to skip
+    // the gamepad subsystem entirely; keyboard + mouse still work.
+    if (getenv("LUMI_NO_GAMEPAD")) return;
+
     SDL_SetHint(SDL_HINT_JOYSTICK_ENHANCED_REPORTS, "1");
     SDL_SetHint(SDL_HINT_JOYSTICK_HIDAPI_STEAM, "1");
     SDL_SetHint(SDL_HINT_JOYSTICK_ROG_CHAKRAM, "1");
@@ -17,8 +24,6 @@ void Input::_init() {
 
     SDL_Init(SDL_INIT_JOYSTICK | SDL_INIT_GAMEPAD);
 
-    inputs.push_back(new InputDevice(InputType::MOUSE_KB));
-
     auto gamePadCount = 0;
     joystickIds = SDL_GetGamepads(&gamePadCount);
 
